For more information on our use of cookies, please refer to our
Cookie Policy
.
Aside from your username, which is required to set up your account and can be fictitious, we won’t display your Personal Information on the Site or reveal it to other Wattpad users (unless you choose to publicly display applicable information via your account settings) or rent or sell it to anyone unless the data has been anonymized. For more information on how signing up to the Wattpad community through third-party social media platforms works, visit our
Signing up with Facebook/Google+ article
.
Except for your email address, date of birth, chosen username, whether you are a reader, writer, or both and at least one preferred literary genre, which are required to create your Wattpad account, you can always opt not to disclose any Personal Information to us, but then you may be unable to use certain features on the Services. For more information, visit our
Account Privacy article
.
