Use of Personal Information
We collect, use, and disclose your Personal Information in accordance with the specific business and commercial purposes below:
Creating your Wattpad account and providing you with our services.
Identifying you across our services (e.g. when you sign in, post a story, or make a comment).
Making age-appropriate content available to you.
Providing you with technical support services.
Communicating with you (e.g., letting you know about upcoming changes or improvements).
Sending you marketing emails, unless you opt-out.
Displaying the information as part of your Wattpad profile.
Calculating anonymous, aggregate statistics to better understand our users, improve our services, and develop new features.
Personalizing and customizing your story discovery experience.
Measuring your use and overall satisfaction with our Services.
Investigating and preventing reported issues, illegal activity, and breaches of our terms of service.
Helping prevent spam, fraud, abuse, and other prohibited activity.
Displaying relevant, tailored advertisements and improving your ad experience.
For security purposes.
Facilitating the connection of third-party services or applications, such as social networks.
Facilitating transactions and payments.
Processing your job application if you apply for a job with us.
De-identifying and aggregating information collected through our services and using it for any lawful purpose.
Contracting with service providers to perform services on our behalf or on their behalf, including maintaining or servicing accounts, providing customer service, processing or fulfilling orders and transactions, verifying customer information, processing payments, providing financing, providing advertising or marketing services, providing analytic services, or providing similar services on behalf of the business or service provider.
For short-term transient use.
Otherwise enabling or effecting, directly or indirectly, a commercial transaction.
For other purposes for which we provide specific notice at the time the information is collected.
